title.narrative: 6.1 CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: EAPR has strengthened evidence, partnerships and resource mobilization capacity to improve CHILD PROTECTION, especially as they relate to children with disabilities Outcomes., which contributes to Access To Justice, Adolescent Empowerment, Children With Disabilities, Evaluation And Research, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: EAPR effectively leverages and utilises resources, strategic partnerships, innovations, data and evidence to drive results for children

description.narrative: UNICEF EAPRO supported four key ASEAN frameworks for child protection on social work, child online protection, migration and bullying. To position ending violence as critical to the recovery from COVID-19, UNICEF EAPRO and WHO collaborated on a region wide conference, attracting high level participants and providing a meaningful platform for the engagement of young people. To support advocacy and programming, EAPRO launched key research initiatives on parenting, VAC-VAW, birth and death registration, legal empowerment and MHPSS. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/03/2022
